/PGH/±ANUKAH/XX672/XX/PR
/KAHADLAKAT NER SHEL H/±ANUKAH //PR
H/±ANUKAH CANDLELIGHTING/XX/PR
Blessed are you, /SCS/XXOURCE OF /XXL/XXIGHT/XX, our God, the sovereign of all
worlds, who has made us holy with your mitzvot, and
commanded us to kindle H/±anukah light./PR
/PR
Blessed are you, /SCT/XXHE /XXR/XXEDEEMER/XX, our God, the sovereign of all
worlds, who wrought wonders for our ancestors in former days
at this time of year./PR
/ITOn the first night of H/±anukah add:/PR
/PR
Blessed are you, /SCE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX, our God, the sovereign of all
worlds, who gave us life, and kept us strong, and brought us to
this time./PR
/PR
/KAMAÚOZ TZUR / ROCK OF AGES/PR
/ITThis translation can be sung to the same melody as the Hebrew./PR
/PR
Rock of Ages, let our song/PR
Praise your saving power;/PR
You amid the raging foes/PR
Were our sheltÚring tower./PR
Furious, they assailed us,/PR
But your arm availed us,/PR
And your word/PR
Broke their sword/PR
When our own strength failed us./PR
Adapted from a translation by Gustav Goøttheil/PR
